# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files specifically.
#   But for an app, you want to ignore it.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/wiki/Common-build-problems#custom-config
#   if you need them.
# pyenv virtualenv
#   The virtual env does not need to be tracked.
#   It's best practice to store the virtual environ
#   elsewhere, or create it on the fly.
#   This config is a common pattern.
#   If you need your own env to be stored in repo,
#   edit accordingly.
#   By default, we ignore it.
#   This line prevents .venv from being tracked.
.venv/
env/
ENV/
env.bak/
# Environments
#   Virtual envs created with venv
#   Usually not committed.
#   If you're using poetry:
poetry.lock
#   pipenv lock file for deterministic builds.
Pipfile.lock
# Secrets
*.env
.env.*
# Node
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-debug.log
yarn-error.log
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
